snippet: The reigning world champion Jordyn Wieber closed out the first day of the United States women’s gymnastics championships in St. Louis tied for first place with Gabrielle Douglas.
abstract: American gymnast Jordyn Wieber, the reigning world champion, closes out the first day of the United States women’s gymnastics championships in St Louis tied for first place with Gabrielle Douglas.
lead_paragraph: The reigning world champion Jordyn Wieber closed out the first day of the United States women’s gymnastics championships in St. Louis tied for first place with Gabrielle Douglas.
